## ğŸ“Œ Overview

This repository contains the official implementation of the paper **"[Insert Your Paper Title]"**.

Standard aerial segmentation models often fail when buildings are viewed from an angle (**oblique**) rather than directly from above (**nadir**). This project solves that problem by fine-tuning YOLOv8 architecture to recognize building "concepts" regardless of the camera perspective.

### Key Features
* âœ… **Perspective Robustness:** Handles high off-nadir angles.
* âœ… **Lightweight:** Runs on standard hardware (no heavy GPU required for inference).
* âœ… **High Precision:** Optimized for distinct building boundaries.

---

## ğŸš€ Proposed Approach

We utilize a modified **YOLOv8-Seg** architecture. The model treats building segmentation as an instance segmentation task, allowing it to separate connected buildings effectively.

